Protocol Decode
Protocol decode extracts parameter values from one or more protocol channels.
The returned values may be assigned directly to wires.
Syntax
Single output channel:
text
params =
.protocol:decode(
  channel
)

Multiple output channels:
text
params =
.protocol:decode(
  channel1,
  channel2,
  ...
)

Channels must be supplied in the same order they were declared in the protocol definition.

───

Runnable — UART
Definition:
text
inline [protocol] .uart8n1:

  tx:
    0
    reverse(data 8b)
    1

:

Decode:
text
8bit data =
.uart8n1:decode(
  0100000101
)

Result:
text
data = ^41


───

Runnable — I2C
Definition:
text
inline [protocol] .i2c:

  clockType: lowFirst

  sda:
    0
    address 7b
    rw 1b
    ack1 1b
    data 8b
    ack2 1b
    1

  scl:
    clock 20b

:

Decode:
text
7bit address,
1bit rw,
1bit ack1,
8bit data,
1bit ack2
=
.i2c:decode(
  sdaBits,
  sclBits
)

Result:
text
address = ^42
rw      = 0
ack1    = 0
data    = ^55
ack2    = 0


───

Decode validation
All protocol-generated segments are verified during decode.
Example:
text
tx:
  0
  reverse(data 8b)
  1

Input:
text
1100000101

Error:
text
Protocol decode failed:
expected start bit '0'
but received '1'


───

Example:
text
scl:
  clock 20b

Input:
text
00000000000000000000

Error:
text
Protocol decode failed:
expected clock waveform


