LUT Decode
LUT decode performs the reverse lookup operation.
Syntax
text
.lut:decode(
  value
)

Optional match index:
text
.lut:decode(
  value,
  matchIndex
)

matchIndex is zero-based.
Default:
text
matchIndex = 0

(first matching entry)

───

Runnable — Unique mapping
Definition:
text
inline [lut] .decoder:
  depth: 4
  length: 16

  data {
    0000 : 0001
    0001 : 0010
    0010 : 0100
  }
:

Decode:
text
4bit x =
.decoder:decode(
  0010
)

Result:
text
0001


───

Runnable — Ambiguous mapping
Definition:
text
inline [lut] .decoder:
  depth: 4
  length: 16

  data {
    0000 : 1111
    0001 : 1111
    0010 : 1111
  }
:

Decode:
text
4bit x =
.decoder:decode(
  1111
)

Result:
text
0000

(first match)

───

Select another match:
text
4bit x =
.decoder:decode(
  1111,
  2
)

Result:
text
0010

(third match)

───

Decode validation
If no matching entry exists:
text
.decoder:decode(
  1010
)

Error:
text
LUT decode failed:
value 1010 does not exist in lookup table


───

If the requested match index is out of range:
text
.decoder:decode(
  1111,
  10
)

Error:
text
LUT decode failed:
match index 10 exceeds available matches (3)


