ASM Decode
ASM decode performs disassembly.
Unlike protocol and LUT decode, ASM decode produces text rather than bit values.
Because the result is textual, it cannot be assigned to wires or memory.
ASM decode may only be used inside debugging functions.

───

Syntax
text
.asmInstance:decode(
  instruction
)


───

Runnable — show()
Definition:
text
inline [asm] .cpu:
  LOAD : 0001 + R2b + A2b
  STORE: 0010 + R2b + A2b
:

Decode:
text
show(
  .cpu:decode(
    00010111
  )
)

Output:
text
LOAD R1 A3


───

Runnable — ROM debugging
text
show(
  .cpu:decode(
    .program:get
  )
)

Output:
text
LOAD R1 A3


───

Invalid usage
ASM decode cannot be assigned.
Invalid:
text
8bit x =
.cpu:decode(
  00010111
)

Error:
text
ASM decode produces text and cannot be assigned to wires


