LUT Labels
Labels provide symbolic names for LUT addresses and values.
They improve readability and allow LUTs to model state machines, token maps, opcode transitions, and other symbolic relationships.
Labels are optional.
There is no panel UI in v1 — logic only.

───

Labels block
Labels are declared before the data {} block.
text
inline [lut] .traffic:

  labels {
    RED    = 00
    YELLOW = 01
    GREEN  = 10
  }

  data {
    RED    : GREEN
    GREEN  : YELLOW
    YELLOW : RED
  }

:


───

Label rules

Rule
Example

Must start with a letter
RED ✓ — 1RED ✗

Letters and digits only
STATE0 ✓ — STATE_A ✗

Unique within the LUT
Duplicate labels are not allowed

Width must match LUT address/value width
RED = 00 ✓



