vs FSM
Many finite state machines can be represented directly using a labeled LUT.
Example:
text
IDLE    : RECEIVE
RECEIVE : STOP
STOP    : IDLE

Because LUT labels are symbolic and isValid() can verify transitions, a separate FSM inline is often unnecessary.
LUT remains the underlying primitive while labels provide a state-oriented view of the same mapping.



