LUT Labels
Labels provide symbolic names for binary values.
Labels may be used with or without a data {} block.
A label behaves like a named constant and may be referenced anywhere a binary value is expected.
There is no panel UI in v1 — logic only.

───

Labels-only LUT
A LUT may contain only labels.
text
inline [lut] .flag:

  ZERO     = 000
  NEGATIVE = 001
  OVERFLOW = 010

:

This LUT acts as a symbolic constant table.

