Using Labels in Expressions
Labels behave like constants and may participate in expressions.
text
inline [lut] .flags:

  ZERO     = 0001
  NEGATIVE = 0010
  OVERFLOW = 0100
  CARRY    = 1000

:

Usage:
text
4wire status =
.flags:ZERO |
.flags:CARRY

Result:
text
1001

Any operator valid for binary values may be used:
text
|
&
!
^

or the equivalent function forms:
text
OR()
AND()
NOT()
XOR()


───

Local Label References
Inside a LUT body, labels may be referenced directly.
Example:
text
inline [lut] .ctrl:

  ACCLOAD = 00000001
  MEMREAD = 00000010

  LOAD = ACCLOAD | MEMREAD

:

Equivalent to:
text
inline [lut] .ctrl:

  ACCLOAD = 00000001
  MEMREAD = 00000010

  LOAD = 00000011

:

The current LUT is searched first.

───

External Label References
Labels from other LUTs may be referenced explicitly.
text
inline [lut] .flags:

  ZERO     = 0001
  OVERFLOW = 0010

:

inline [lut] .status:

  ERROR = .flags:OVERFLOW

:

External references always use:
text
.lutName:LABEL


