fără data {} → tabel de constante
cu data {} → tabel de mapare
cu isValid() → validator de tranziții
cu decode() → reverse lookup
cu labeluri → enum-uri și state-uri
cu expresii → flags și control words

=====.
LUT Constant Expressions
LUT labels and data {} values may contain constant expressions.
Expressions are evaluated at parse time and produce a binary value.
In addition to the computed value, the original expression AST is preserved for debugging, documentation, show(), probe(), and future logic analyzer integrations.

───

Supported operators
The following operators are supported:
text
|
&
!

Meaning:
text
A | B

Bitwise OR.
text
A & B

Bitwise AND.
text
!A

Bitwise NOT.

───

Examples
OR
text
inline [lut] .ctrl:

  ACCLOAD = 00000001
  MEMREAD = 00000010

  LOAD = ACCLOAD | MEMREAD

:

Computed value:
text
00000011

Stored expression:
text
ACCLOAD | MEMREAD


───

AND
text
inline [lut] .mask:

  USER = 1111
  VISIBLE = 1010

  RESULT = USER & VISIBLE

:

Computed value:
text
1010

Stored expression:
text
USER & VISIBLE


───

NOT
text
inline [lut] .flags:

  WRITE = 0010
  ALL = 1111

  USER = ALL & !WRITE

:

Computed value:
text
1101

Stored expression:
text
ALL & !WRITE


───

Parentheses
Parentheses may be used to explicitly group expressions.
Example:
text
RESULT =
(A | B | C)
&
!D


───

Expressions in labels
Labels may be defined using constant expressions.
text
inline [lut] .ctrl:

  ACCLOAD = 00000001
  MEMREAD = 00000010

  LOAD = ACCLOAD | MEMREAD

:

Equivalent value:
text
LOAD = 00000011


───

Expressions in data {}
Expressions may also appear on the value side of LUT mappings.
text
inline [lut] .ctrl:

  ACCLOAD = 00000001
  MEMREAD = 00000010

  data {
    LOAD : ACCLOAD | MEMREAD
  }

:

Equivalent mapping:
text
LOAD : 00000011


───

Debugging
The computed binary value is used during execution.
The original expression is preserved for debugging.
Example:
text
LOAD = ACCLOAD | MEMREAD

Possible debug output:
text
LOAD
ACCLOAD | MEMREAD
00000011


───

doc()
Possible output:
text
LOAD = ACCLOAD | MEMREAD
       00000011

USER = ALL & !WRITE
       1101

This preserves both:
• the symbolic meaning
• the final binary value

───

Notes
Constant expressions are intended for:
• CPU control words
• microcode tables
• status flags
• interrupt masks
• permissions
• protocol constants
• symbolic bit masks
The expression is evaluated once at parse time and never at runtime.
